</md></sn><sn><md>### 05 : Double,Triple,Quaruple of Profit-Principle {.text-center}


**Equation and Fact :**

- rate of profit for profit-pincipal to be N times of principal<br>
What must be the rate of simple interest per annum for any principal to N times itself in $n$ years?<br>
let the principal is 100<br>
profit_principle = $N \times 100$<br>
profit = profit_principle - principle <br>
profit = $N \times 100 - 100$ = $100(N-1)$ <br>
rate of profit $r= \frac{I \times 100}{pn}$ <br>
rate of profit $r= \frac{100(N-1) \times 100}{100n}$ <br>
rate of profit $r= \frac{N-1 \times 100}{n}$ <br>
rate of profit $r= \frac{N-1}{n} \times 100$ <br>

- n year for profit-pincipal to be N times of principal at r profit rate<br>
let the principal is 100<br>
profit_principle = $N \times 100$<br>
profit = profit_principle - principle <br>
profit = $N \times 100 - 100$ = $100(N-1)$ <br>
time $r= \frac{I \times 100}{pr}$ <br>
time profit $r= \frac{100(N-1) \times 100}{100r}$ <br>
time $r= \frac{N-1 \times 100}{r}$ <br>
time $r= \frac{N-1}{r} \times 100$ <br>



**Type of Question :**
- determining rate
- determining time
- multiple application


#### Math

**67.** At what simple interest rate per annum will any principal double itself in $8$ years?<br>
[Biman Bangladesh Airlines (Traffic Helper)-2024] + [BPC (Upper Division Assistant)-2024]

* a. 10%
* b. 11.5%
* c. `12.5%`
* d. 13%

+++ Solution:
Let the Principal be $P$.<br>
If the principal doubles itself, the Total Amount becomes $2P$.

- $\text{Interest (I)} = 2P - P = P$
- $R = \frac{I \times 100}{P \times T} = \frac{P \times 100}{P \times 8} = \frac{100}{8} = 12.5\%$
+++

**69.** At $12.5\%$ annual simple interest, in how many years will the interest be equal to the principal?<br>
[CAAB (Aerodrome/Inspector/Assistant Store Officer)-2021]

* a. 4
* b. `8`
* c. 7
* d. 5

+++ Solution:
Let the principal be $P$.
Since the interest is equal to the principal, Interest ($I$) = $P$. <br>
Given, Rate of interest ($r$) = $12.5\%$ <br>
We know,

- $I = \frac{P \times r \times t}{100}$
- $P = \frac{P \times 12.5 \times t}{100}$
- $1 = \frac{12.5 \times t}{100}$
- $t = \frac{100}{12.5} = 8\text{ years}$
+++

