* d. `10`</md></sn><sn><md>#### 06 : Determination of Principle{.text-center}

**Equation and Fact :**
- Principal $P = \frac{I \times 100}{rn}$
- Profit_principal $A = P + I$ <br>
  $A = P + Prn$ <br>
  $A = P(1+rn)$ <br>
  $P = \frac{A}{1+n\frac{r}{100}}$ <br>
  $P = \frac{A}{\frac{100+nr}{100}}$ <br>
  $P = \frac{A \times 100}{100+nr}$
- Getting time from profit-principal <br>
  Profit_principal $A = P+I$<br>
  $A = P+Prn$<br>
  $A = P(1+rn)$<br>
  $\frac{A}{P} = 1+rn$<br>
  $1+rn = \frac{A}{P}$<br>
  $rn = \frac{A}{P} - 1$<br>
  times $n = \frac{\frac{A}{P} - 1}{r} \times 100$

- Principal is the 100% amount that we invest in,if it is not given we can consider it as 100
- It is fixed in simple profit
- For monthly profit $n = \frac{1}{2}$

**Types of Math**
- Profit is given
- Profit_principle is given

