**Equation and Facts :**

- Interest is $\frac{x}{y}$ of principal,what is the principal amount?<br>
  Let principal = $P$ <br>
  Interest = $\frac{x}{y} \text{of} P$<br>
  Interest = $\frac{Px}{y}$<br>
  Now $A = P + I$<br>
  $A = P + \frac{Px}{y}$  <br>
  evaluate P
- The interest is what portion of principal<br>
  $\frac{I}{P} = ?$

- For what rate of interest the interest for 1 years will be $\frac{1}{5}$ of principal?<br>
  $\frac{I}{P} = \frac{1}{5}$ so $P=5I$ <br>
  Now, $r=\frac{I \times 100}{Pn}$ <br>
  $r =\frac{I \times 100}{Pn}$ <br>
  $r =\frac{I \times 100}{5In}$ <br>
  $r =\frac{100}{5n}$ <br>
  $r =\frac{100}{\text{X}n}$ <br>
  X : 
  - what time principal is larger than interest or
  - interest is what portion of principal <br>
    Use standard equation instead of this shortcut as it may sometimes introduce invalid calculation,use shortcut to double check

- interest is $\frac{x}{y}$ of principal<br>
  interest is $\frac{x}{y}$ of profit-principal<br>
  both are not equal,be caution on this


