* d. Principal 300; Interest rate 9%</md></sn><sn><md>### 08 : Increase or Decrease of rate of profit {.text-center}

**Fact and Equation**

Rate of profit decreases from **x%** to **y%**, so the annual profit decreases by **M Tk.** What is the principal?<br>
$(x-y)\%$ decrease = Corresponding decrease in annual profit <br>
$D\% = M$ <br>
$1\% = \frac{M}{D}$ <br>
$100\% = \frac{M}{D} \times 100$ <br>
Here, **100% represents the principal.**

If the problem gives a period of **n years** instead of **1 year**, then:<br>
$n \times (x-y)\%$ = Corresponding decrease in profit for **n years** <br>
$n \times D\% = M$ <br>
$1\% = \frac{M}{D}$ <br>
$100\% = \frac{M}{D} \times 100$ <br>

:::.p-3 .border
So the Equation is : <br>
principal = $\frac{M \times 100}{D}$ <br>
M : corresponding money in n years <br>
D : $n \times ( x - y)$
:::

